The Lodger: A Story of the London Fog

Review: Hypnotic visuals capturing abundant detail and its atmosphere in a natural, slow, everyday pace without much of a story to tell. The use of space and scenography is just stunning, I’ll return to this film when I need to pause time for a while. It sent me into a meditative state watching it, like I’m just living for the moment, living for the drop of Papaya juice in childlike wonder.
